<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="590" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1652,2038]" pageId="3" pageNumber="590">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,1796,1822]" pageId="3" pageNumber="590">Comments.</emphasis>
The first and so far the only record of this species from 
<collectingCountry box="[977,1059,1796,1822]" name="Taiwan" pageId="3" pageNumber="590">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
is a male from 
<collectingRegion box="[1237,1322,1796,1822]" country="Taiwan" name="Taitung" pageId="3" pageNumber="590">Taitung</collectingRegion>
(southern Taiwan) mentioned by 
<bibRefCitation author="Gentili, E." box="[412,575,1832,1859]" pageId="3" pageNumber="590" refId="ref7656" refString="Gentili, E. (2003) Hydrophilidae: III. Additional noteson the genus Laccobius Erichson in China and neighbouring areas (Coleoptera). In: Jach, M. A. &amp; Ji, L. (Eds.), Water beetles of China, Volume 3. Zoologisch-Botanische Gesellschaft in Osterreich and Wiener Coleopterologenverein, Wien, pp. 411 - 429. [vi + 572 pp.]" type="book" year="2003">Gentili (2003)</bibRefCitation>
. This species is very similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gentili" authorityYear="1979" box="[931,1065,1832,1858]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrophilidae" genus="Laccobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="590" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="formosus">
<emphasis box="[931,1065,1832,1858]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="590">L. formosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and can be differentiated by the narrower median lobe of the aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[591,674,1868,1895]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–18" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1423,1447]" captionTargetBox="[163,1412,192,1363]" captionTargetId="figure-24@4.[151,1436,181,1400]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 10–18. Dosal view of the habitus and male genitalia of Taiwanese Laccobius species (10–13: habitus, 14–18: male genitalia). 10, 14: L. politus Gentili, 1979. 11, 15: L. formosus Gentili, 1979. 12, 16: L. hammondi Gentili, 1984. 13, 17: L. roseiceps Régimbart, 1903. 18: L. fragilis Nakane, 1966, after Nakane (1966)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4704291" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4704291/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="590">Fig. 18</figureCitation>
). We did not find any specimens of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Gentili" authorityYear="2003" box="[1074,1184,1868,1894]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrophilidae" genus="Laccobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="590" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fragilis">
<emphasis box="[1074,1184,1868,1894]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="590">L. fragilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in this study, although we also examined specimens from 
<collectingRegion box="[543,632,1904,1930]" country="Taiwan" name="Taitung" pageId="3" pageNumber="590">Taitung</collectingRegion>
. The occurrence of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Gentili" authorityYear="2003" box="[852,963,1904,1930]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrophilidae" genus="Laccobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="590" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fragilis">
<emphasis box="[852,963,1904,1930]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="590">L. fragilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingCountry box="[998,1080,1904,1930]" name="Taiwan" pageId="3" pageNumber="590">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
hence needs to be reconfirmed. However, more species usually co-occur at localities sampled by us in 
<collectingCountry box="[941,1023,1940,1966]" name="Taiwan" pageId="3" pageNumber="590">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
and we hence cannot exclude that 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Gentili" authorityYear="2003" class="Insecta" family="Hydrophilidae" genus="Laccobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="590" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fragilis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="590">L. fragilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may be rare and hence unrecorded by us. Therefore, we still maintain 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Gentili" authorityYear="2003" box="[1023,1133,1976,2002]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrophilidae" genus="Laccobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="590" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fragilis">
<emphasis box="[1023,1133,1976,2002]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="590">L. fragilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a member of Taiwanese fauna.
</paragraph>
